<p id="fs-idp42982896">Is the self-ionization of water endothermic or exothermic? The ionization constant for water (<em data-effect="italics">K</em><sub>w</sub>) is 2.9 <math display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mo>×</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mo>×</mo></annotation-xml></semantics></math> 10<sup>−14</sup> at 40 °C and 9.3 <math display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mo>×</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mo>×</mo></annotation-xml></semantics></math> 10<sup>−14</sup> at 60 °C.</p></div></div>
