<p id="fs-idm102500016">The odor of vinegar is due to the presence of acetic acid, CH<sub>3</sub>CO<sub>2</sub>H, a weak acid. List, in order of descending concentration, all of the ionic and molecular species present in a 1-<em data-effect="italics">M</em> aqueous solution of this acid.</p>
</div></div>

</div>
<div class=" " data-type="exercise" id="fs-idm81289984">
<div data-type="problem" id="fs-idm81289728"><span class="os-number">30</span><span class="os-divider">. </span><div class="os-problem-container">
