<p id="fs-idp54393232">What is the ionization constant at 25 °C for the weak acid <math display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mrow/><msub><mrow><mtext>NH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mrow/><msup><mrow/><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo>,</mo></mrow></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>CH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mrow/><msub><mrow><mtext>NH</mtext></mrow><mn>3</mn></msub><mrow/><msup><mrow/><mtext>+</mtext></msup><mo>,</mo></mrow></annotation-xml></semantics></math> the conjugate acid of the weak base CH<sub>3</sub>NH<sub>2</sub>, <em data-effect="italics">K</em><sub>b</sub> = 4.4 <math display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mo>×</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mo>×</mo></annotation-xml></semantics></math> 10<sup>−4</sup>.</p>
