<p id="fs-idm103659360">Explain why the pH does not change significantly when a small amount of an acid or a base is added to a solution that contains equal amounts of the acid H<sub>3</sub>PO<sub>4</sub> and a salt of its conjugate base NaH<sub>2</sub>PO<sub>4</sub>.</p>
</div></div>

