<p id="fs-idm64046528">A buffer solution is prepared from equal volumes of 0.200 <em data-effect="italics">M</em> acetic acid and 0.600 <em data-effect="italics">M</em> sodium acetate. Use 1.80 <math display="inline"><semantics><mrow><mo>×</mo></mrow><annotation-xml encoding="MathML-Content"><mo>×</mo></annotation-xml></semantics></math> 10<sup>−5</sup> as <em data-effect="italics">K</em><sub>a</sub> for acetic acid.</p>
